# Receiving an error message when trying to run Windows Update so, we need to do this steps:

You will need to run windows update troubleshooting.
Make sure you have free space in your hard drive for windows update.
Install updates manually.
Also, you could visit that website for getting more information
https://4sysops.com/archives/seven-ways-to-fix-windows-update-if-it-fails-or-is-not-working-at-all/

Disconnect external hardware
Run device manger then look for any device with yellow mark and update the driver.
Repair hard drive errors thought the command line you will need to log in as administrator then type chkdsk/f c: then press enter so, repairs will automatically run.
For more information please check this website 
https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/troubleshoot-problems-updating-windows-188c2b0f-10a7-d72f-65b8-32d177eb136c#WindowsVersion=Windows_10


